    <title>Cyberpunk 2077 is CD Projekt Red’s biggest game ever, despite its disastrous launch</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/essEGtdiJZkkil_n0CSOCWCFvEI=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/69169934/Cyberpunk2077_Im_your_fixer_RGB_en.0.jpeg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;A screenshot from &lt;/em&gt;Cyberpunk 2077&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt; | Image: CD Projekt Red&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="cj0Mq9"&gt;Despite &lt;em&gt;Cyberpunk 2077&lt;/em&gt;’s disastrous and bug-filled December 10th launch, the title was “the largest game in CD Projekt Red’s history,” &lt;a href="https://www.cdprojekt.com/en/wp-content/uploads-en/2021/04/press-release-2020-results.pdf"&gt;the studio said on Thursday (PDF)&lt;/a&gt;. The game sold 13.7 million copies in 2020, according to CD Projekt Red.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="RAwH7a"&gt;We already had a pretty good idea that &lt;em&gt;Cyberpunk 2077&lt;/em&gt; has been a major financial success for the studio. On December 9th, one day before the game’s launch, CD Projekt Red announced that &lt;em&gt;Cyberpunk 2077&lt;/em&gt; had accrued &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/CDPROJEKTRED_IR/status/1336941257965375489"&gt;8 million preorders&lt;/a&gt;. One day after the game’s release, CD Projekt Red said digital preorders &lt;a href="https://www.cdprojekt.com/en/investors/regulatory-announcements/current-report-no-65-2020/"&gt;had recouped&lt;/a&gt; all of the game’s development and marketing costs. And the studio said that the game had sold more than 13 million copies as of December 20th in a &lt;a href="https://www.cdprojekt.com/en/investors/regulatory-announcements/current-report-no-67-2020/"&gt;memo shared on December 22nd&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="WtK1gL"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cyberpunk...&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
